author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Strong corporate earnings gives boost to Dow
text:
ANDREW GOMBERT/EPA The S&P climbed 1.7% on Thursday, and has now regained nearly all it lost when stocks tumbled in August. Upbeat corporate earnings and positive economic data helped boost the Dow more than 300 points and lift the S&P 500 to a two-month high.
Better than expected quarterly results Thursday from McDonaldâ€™s, eBay and United Airlines buoyed investors. The S&P climbed 1.7% and has now regained nearly all it lost when stocks swooned in August.
Separate reports showed U.S. home resales grew 5% in September while jobless claims remained around a 42-year low last week.
